{{!--
  ============================================================================
  DEFINITIONS & INTERPRETATION SECTION
  Standard legal definitions for tenancy agreements across all UK jurisdictions

  USAGE (HTML):
  {{> definitions_section}}

  NOTES:
  - Jurisdiction-specific terms can be passed as parameters
  - This creates defined terms that should be used consistently throughout the agreement
  ============================================================================
--}}

{{#*inline "definitions_section"}}
<section class="definitions-section">
  <h2>Definitions and Interpretation</h2>

  <p>In this Agreement, unless the context requires otherwise, the following definitions apply:</p>

  <ul class="definitions-list">
    <li>
      <span class="defined-term">"Agreement"</span> means this tenancy agreement and any schedules attached hereto.
    </li>
    <li>
      <span class="defined-term">"Landlord"</span> means {{landlord_full_name}} and includes their successors in title, assigns, and any person or company entitled to possession of the Property on termination of the Tenancy.
    </li>
    {{#if agent_name}}
    <li>
      <span class="defined-term">"Agent"</span> means {{agent_name}}, the Landlord's authorised managing agent, and includes their successors in business.
    </li>
    {{/if}}
    <li>
      <span class="defined-term">"Tenant"</span> means {{#if multiple_tenants}}jointly and severally{{/if}} {{#each tenants}}{{this.full_name}}{{#unless @last}}, {{/unless}}{{/each}}.
    </li>
    {{#if guarantor_name}}
    <li>
      <span class="defined-term">"Guarantor"</span> means {{guarantor_name}}.
    </li>
    {{/if}}
    <li>
      <span class="defined-term">"Property"</span> means the dwelling at {{property_address}} including all fixtures, fittings, and contents as set out in Schedule 1 and any inventory provided.
    </li>
    <li>
      <span class="defined-term">"Term"</span> means the {{#if is_fixed_term}}fixed term period commencing on {{tenancy_start_date}} and ending on {{tenancy_end_date}}, and any periodic tenancy that may arise thereafter{{else}}periodic tenancy commencing on {{tenancy_start_date}}{{/if}}.
    </li>
    <li>
      <span class="defined-term">"Rent"</span> means the sum of {{currency_symbol}}{{rent_amount}} per {{rent_period}}, payable in accordance with Schedule 2.
    </li>
    <li>
      <span class="defined-term">"Deposit"</span> means the sum of {{currency_symbol}}{{deposit_amount}} held as security in accordance with Schedule 2 and protected under the {{deposit_scheme_name}}.
    </li>
    <li>
      <span class="defined-term">"Scheme"</span> means the government-authorised tenancy deposit protection scheme in which the Deposit is registered, being {{deposit_scheme_name}}.
    </li>
    <li>
      <span class="defined-term">"Contents"</span> means the furniture, furnishings, and other items provided by the Landlord for use by the Tenant as specified in any inventory.
    </li>
    <li>
      <span class="defined-term">"Schedule"</span> means a schedule attached to this Agreement, which forms part of and is incorporated into this Agreement.
    </li>
    <li>
      <span class="defined-term">"Written Notice"</span> means a notice in writing delivered by hand, sent by first-class post to the address given in this Agreement, or sent by email to an email address provided by the recipient{{#if email_notices_permitted}} (email notices are permitted under this Agreement){{/if}}.
    </li>
    <li>
      <span class="defined-term">"Working Day"</span> means any day other than a Saturday, Sunday, or public holiday in {{jurisdiction_name}}.
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Interpretation</h3>

  <ul class="definitions-list">
    <li>
      References to statutes or statutory provisions include any statutory modification, re-enactment, or subordinate legislation in force from time to time.
    </li>
    <li>
      Words importing the singular include the plural and vice versa; words importing any gender include all genders.
    </li>
    <li>
      The headings in this Agreement are for convenience only and shall not affect its interpretation.
    </li>
    <li>
      Where there is more than one Tenant, their obligations and liabilities under this Agreement are joint and several.
    </li>
    <li>
      Any obligation on a party not to do something includes an obligation not to allow or permit that thing to be done.
    </li>
  </ul>
</section>
{{/inline}}

